Aberdeenshire Council warns of £28m of savings
Aberdeenshire Council has warned that it faces having to make more than £28m of savings this year.Councillors willbe told next weekthat the proposed savings for 2016/17 run to £28.3m.More than £6m of the savings had to be identified after details of the recentlocal government funding settlementwere announced.By 2021 it is being predicted there could be a funding shortfall of more than £45m.